on: Solutions to make it fair</span><hr size=1> The strategy that respec takes out is certainly an arguement against it/an arguement for a one time wipe, which means that templates can't be planned with respec in mind.<br>
AO had a fairly good idea when they did their respec (Granted, AO has a LOT more skills to train in for each class)<br>
They allowed everyone the opportunity to do a complete wipe of points for a limited period of time, then introduced a  system of reset points gained at certain levels, each of which would let you reset a certain skill.  Due to the number of skills you needed to train (Too large for the reset points to allow you to completely change paths - Plus there typically aren't as many viable paths.  Which is a bad thing in itself), this worked well for them.<br>
<br>
A one time reset, taking into account auto-points if you had them (And setting a flag if you didn't, to prevent you from getting extra points from autoing after the wipe) would seem the most effective solution to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.showPrevMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.showNextMessage?topicID=2.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=0><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub11.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="yinyangofcamelotfrm16">Ideas, Balance, General Discussion<option value="